From 70639db7a352ea7e13a48a8b43946f65432947f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CarolinePascal <caroline8.pascal@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 15:20:08 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] perf(rbd): cooperative PGS solves + integrate
 (threads(32), bit-identical)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Continues the per-env-parallelism work: converts the remaining hot threads(1)
multibody kernels to cooperative threads(32) (one workgroup per articulation).
All bit-identical (gather err 0.0). Lifts native-CUDA biped to 63.6k env/s
@ N=8192 (from 60.8k; baseline 45k), Isaac gap 4.8x -> 3.2x.

- joint/contact PGS sweeps (remove_solve_joint_no_bias, solve_contact,
  remove_solve_contact): Gauss-Seidel across constraints stays serial, but each
  constraint's J·v reduction + O(ndofs) DOF-apply is split across lanes — lane 0
  forms the scalar impulse delta (+ free-body update / friction clamp) and
  broadcasts it via a workgroup buffer, all lanes apply disjoint DOFs, one
  barrier per constraint. New solve_joint_constraints_par / contact variant;
  init_solve phase-3 now uses the cooperative joint solve too. joint PGS ~3.4x;
  contact PGS ~1.3x (reduction-barrier overhead at small contact counts).
- gpu_mb_integrate: lane-split over links (disjoint workspaces, no barriers) ~1.9x.
- host: all launched with ThreadCount = multibodies_per_batch * MB_LU_LANES.

gpu_mb_gravity_and_lu / compute_dynamics_pre were already cooperative. The one
remaining threads(1) builder is gpu_mb_init_contact_constraints (jacobian fill
needs the walk's per-contact geometry — phase-split deferred).

